items.sentence: You know that they won't let you do that, don't you?
You do know that I don't want to do that, don't you?
You didn't know that you needed to do that, did you?
You didn't know I was the one who did that, did you?
You didn't know I had to do that by myself, did you?
All the women in the room screamed at the same time.
Nothing could be heard but the ticking of the clock.
Tom realized he wasn't likely to be able to do that.
Tom painted the chairs and the table the same color.
The last time that we were here was three weeks ago.
